jobData.description:
•	Provides coverage for member services at multiple recreation centers to ensure operational continuity.
•	Processes entry for members and guests, facilitating efficient access to facilities.
•	Delivers general information and guided tours to promote understanding and engagement with recreation center services.
•	Manages telephone inquiries, including the processing of phone payments to accommodate remote transactions.
•	Conducts sales of memberships and day passes, contributing to revenue growth and community participation.
•	Operates front desk autonomously, demonstrating reliability and the ability to manage tasks independently.
•	Able to manage immediate operations of front desk when management is away for whatever reason
•	Creates weekend room rental reference sheets, ensuring both print accessibility and compliance with Section 508 standards.
•	Trains new employees in the use of ActiveNet, enhancing team competence and service quality.
•	Worker at a Municipal Emergency Shelter during extreme weather conditions
•	Opens and Closes the Front Desk at the beginning and end of the day
